  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An extensive uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted across all five flow-speed operating points, including Latin-hypercube sampling over geometric tolerances and fluid-property uncertainties; results confirmed that the hemolysis index remains below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold across the sampled space. Sensitivity rankings derived from the UQ campaign are documented in the validation report and informed factor weighting throughout this assessment.",
