      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) computed across coarse, medium, and fine meshes (4.2 M, 12.1 M, 31.8 M cells). GCI for hemolysis index < 2.1% on fine mesh. Discretization error within acceptable bounds for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-02-bench-hemolysis",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-top hemolysis validation against modified index of hemolysis (MIH) measurements",
      "description": "CFD-predicted MIH compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed operating points. Relative error < 15% at all points; mean absolute relative error 8.3%. Validation activities conducted in blood-analog fluid at physiologic hematocrit. The UQ campaign embedded within this validation sweep confirmed that geometric tolerance variations of ±0.05 mm produce less than 4% change in predicted RH, corroborating model robustness. Sensitivity findings are fully narrated in the attached validation report (DOI 10.1016/j.jbiomech.2023.morrison)."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-predicate-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
